Day 5 — Cybersecurity Journey 🌐🔍

Today I explored Nmap, one of the most powerful tools used in cybersecurity and penetration testing. I learned the basics of both the GUI version and CLI commands to understand how network scanning and reconnaissance work.

Topics I Learned
Introduction to Nmap GUI & CLI
Host discovery and network scanning
Basic port scanning techniques
Understanding open, closed, and filtered ports
Service and version detection
Common Nmap commands and flags
Importance of reconnaissance in penetration testing
Basic Commands Practiced
nmap <target>
nmap -sV <target>
nmap -A <target>
nmap -Pn <target>
nmap -p 80,443 <target>
Key Takeaways
Reconnaissance is the foundation of ethical hacking.
Nmap helps identify services, ports, and potential attack surfaces.
Learning CLI commands improves efficiency and understanding of network scanning.

Every day I’m getting closer to becoming a skilled penetration tester by strengthening my practical cybersecurity knowledge. 🚀🔐

